      "value": "<p>&gt;@UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.On2ZrPJTe8FURsXY]{Operative Exploit}</p>\n<p>For your debilitating trick, you can attempt to knock the target prone. The target must succeed at a @Check[type:reflex] save or fall @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.conditions.XeRGqHVtcZ7vsgJ0]{Prone}. If the target gains a bonus to its KAC against @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.rules.U37n5tY5hn1ctzQL.JournalEntryPage.R33uiOMesYP0ISWl#trip]{Trip} combat maneuvers, it adds this bonus to its saving throw, and if it is immune to the trip combat maneuver it is immune to this operative exploit. Once youâ€™ve used this ability to attempt to knock a target prone, that creature is immune to your knee shot for 24 hours. This exploit counts as @UUID[Compendium.sfrpg.class-features.o2GDNS1g87yquIMS]{Staggering Shot (Ex)} for the purpose of meeting the prerequisites of other operative exploits.</p>"
